            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha ye ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               1 INTRODUCTION

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               This document describes the interface, installation, and
               usage requirements for

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the Tritium Battery Management System (BMS).

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMS provides an easy way to monitor and control an
               Electric Vehicle battery

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               pack, and can work seamlessly with Tritium's WaveSculptor
               motor controllers. It

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               is a mature design with five previous product generations
               of real-world

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               experience with various types of cells, form factors, and
               vehicles.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y60 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMS consists of two components: multiple Cell
               Management Units (CMU),

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y61 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               which measure and control the individual cells in the
               battery pack; and a single

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y62 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               BMS Master Unit(BMU) which interfaces between the CMUs
               and the vehicle,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y63 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               controls precharge and other safety systems, and provides
               total pack telemetry.

            .. container:: t m0 x6 h8 yc ff2 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               4 of 29

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha ye ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               2 BMS FUNCTION

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The function of the BMS is threefold, in order of
               priority:

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y65 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Monitorcell voltages and temperatures, and act on this
               information to

            .. container:: t m0 x9 h4 y5c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               protect the pack against being operated outside
               acceptable limits

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y66 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Managethe cells, to keep them at equal state of charge
               (SOC)

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y67 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Reporttelemetry to the other systems in the vehicle, to
               allow a graceful

            .. container:: t m0 x9 h4 y68 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               reduction in vehicle performance as the battery
               approaches its limits

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y69 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMS performs these functions by measuring the
               following parameters:

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y6a ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Individual cell voltages

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y6b ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Group cell temperatures

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y17 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •CMU temperatures

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y6c ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Total pack voltage

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y6d ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Total DC bus voltage

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y6e ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Total pack current

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y6f ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Isolation from chassis

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y70 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •12V supply voltages and currents

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y71 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Contactor status

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y72 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Fan / Pump speeds

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y73 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               To achieve management over the cells and pack, it
               controls:

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y74 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Individual cell bypass (shunt) balance resistors

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y75 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Pack contactors, including precharging HV loads

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y76 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Battery pack fan / pump

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y77 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Battery charger charging current setpoint

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y78 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Individual cell voltages are the most critical
               measurement taken by the system,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y79 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               and in the Tritium BMS are measured using two separate,
               redundant circuits,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y7a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               each with it's own analog circuitry, A/D converter, and
               reference.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y7b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               All measurements are cross-checked, and any fault in the
               system can be

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y7c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               identified and reported. This system not only gives
               reliable and accurate cell

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y7d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               voltage measurements, it gives trusted measurements.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y7e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The Tritium BMS reports if any measurements are not
               trustworthy, and this

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y7f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               information can be acted on by a higher-level system in
               the vehicle, for instance

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y80 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               by notifying the driver that the vehicle requires
               servicing.

            .. container:: t m0 x6 h8 yc ff2 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               3 WARNINGS

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               A properly designed BMS system will protect a battery
               pack from being operated

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               outside of acceptable limits. However, a poorly
               implemented system may not

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y82 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               provide the expected protection – the Tritium BMS must be
               installed in a

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y83 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               professional and competent manner to function as
               designed.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Attention should also be paid to the larger system that
               the vehicle is part of,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               especially the systems associated with charging and the
               infrastructure to support

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y84 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               it. As well as using the BMS to protect the pack,
               additional systems should be

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y85 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               provided as backup as part of the charging
               infrastructure, for instance: fitting of

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y86 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               smoke detectors; overcurrent and RCD protection in the AC
               supply; regular

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y87 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               physical checks of charge cabling and connections;
               regular review of telemetry

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y88 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               data for abnormal readings.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y89 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               This list is not exhaustive, and it is the responsibility
               of the system designer /

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y8a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               installer to conduct their own failure mode analysis and
               determine what is

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y8b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               required.

            .. container:: t m0 xa h4 y8c ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Working around batteries is DANGEROUS.

            .. container:: t m0 xb h4 y8d ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Not only are lethal high voltages present, but individual
               cells can also

            .. container:: t m0 xc h4 y8e ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               put out thousands of amps when shorted, for example with
               a stray wire

            .. container:: t m0 xd h4 y8f ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               or dropped tool, throwing out arcs and molten metal.

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y90 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Check the legal requirements in your jurisdiction for
               using licensed

            .. container:: t m0 xe h4 y91 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               technicians for this type of work.

            .. container:: t m0 xf h4 y92 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Wear eye protection. Use insulated tools. Take extreme
               caution.

            .. container:: t m0 x10 h4 y93 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Go slow. Think through every step before doing it.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y94 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               4 TERMINOLOGY

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y95 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Cell:A single physical unit, or permanently connected
               parallel group of

            .. container:: t m0 x11 h4 y96 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               units. A parallel group functions electrically as a
               larger capacity

            .. container:: t m0 x11 h4 y97 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               single unit.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y98 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Battery:A series-connected group of cells

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha ye ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               5 CELL MANAGEMENT UNIT

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y9a ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               5.1FORM FACTOR

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y9b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The Cell Management Unit (CMU) is supplied as a 1.6mm
               thickness Printed Circuit

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y9c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Board (PCB), conformally coated, without an enclosure. It
               is designed to be

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y9d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               installed inside the battery box, in a weather-sealed
               area, along with the cells

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y9e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               themselves. This means that all connections to the cells
               remain inside the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y9f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               battery pack enclosure, simplifying fusing and wiring
               installation requirements.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha ya0 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               5.2INSTALLATION

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ya1 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The CMU should be mounted to a flat surface, using at
               least four M3 fasteners,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ya2 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               with the supplied piece of insulation material between
               the CMU and the surface.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ya3 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The CMU will operate at a much lower temperature when
               balancing if the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ya4 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               mounting surface is a thermally conductive material such
               as aluminium or steel,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ya5 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               and it is strongly recommended to install the CMUs on a
               surface such as this.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ya6 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               CMUs should not be stacked together, as they will
               overheat.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ya7 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               For a professional installation, press-fit M3 studs (eg
               PEM FHS-M3-10) can be

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ya8 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               installed in the wall of the box prior to fitting the
               CMUs. The insulating sheet and

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ya9 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               CMU are then installed over the studs, and retained in
               place with Nyloc nuts.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y42 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Wiring should be appropriately strain relieved to
               withstand the vibration typically

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yaa ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               found in an automotive environment – do not support the
               weight of the wiring

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yab ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               loom solely from the connectors on the CMU.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha yac ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               5.3DIMENSIONS

            .. container:: t m0 x6 h8 yc ff2 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               7 of 29

               5.4CONNECTORS OVERVIEW

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yae ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The following illustration shows the connections and
               indicators on the CMU:

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha yaf ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               5.5ISOLATION

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yb0 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The CMU is isolated from the CMU CAN bus, and therefore
               from the vehicle

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yb1 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               chassis and other CMUs, with an isolation barrier rated
               for 1000V DC. This allows

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yb2 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the HV battery pack to be fully floating from the vehicle
               chassis, as is required by

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yb3 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               most EV construction standards (eg NCOP14 in Australia).

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yb4 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               This isolation barrier rating is only valid if the
               correct insulation material is

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yb5 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               installed between the CMU and the surface it is mounted
               on.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yb6 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               As the CMU CAN bus operates relative to the vehicle
               chassis, the CMU CAN ribbon

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yb7 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               cable should be kept isolated from the cells and cell
               sense wiring with a rating of

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yb8 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               at least the full voltage of the battery pack.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha yb9 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               5.6VOLTAGE RATING

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yba ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The CMU voltage sense inputs are rated for a maximum of
               5V per cell. Therefore,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ybb ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               there must not be any breaks in the main battery string
               (from contactors, fuses,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ybc ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               or service links) among the set of up to eight cells that
               are measured by a CMU,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ybd ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               as a high voltage may be seen across this break when it
               is open, and destroy the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ybe ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               CMU. Any breaks must be located between CMUs.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha ybf ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               5.7INDICATORS

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yc0 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The green LED on the CMU flashes to indicate that the CMU
               has power (via the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yc1 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               CMU CAN bus) and the microcontroller is operating.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yc2 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The red LED illuminates when any of the eight cells are
               balancing. This LED

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yc3 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               illuminating is not a fault condition.

            .. container:: t m0 x6 h8 yc ff2 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               8 of 29

               5.8CELL VOLTAGE & TEMPERATURE SENSE CONNECTOR

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yae ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The connector used for the Cell Voltage Sense is a 12-way
               single-row 3mm pitch

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ycc ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Molex MicroFit connector. The pinout is shown below, as
               viewed from the wire

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ycd ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               side – as you would look at it while inserting crimps.
               The colours shown match

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yce ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               those used in the recommended cable.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ycf ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Please refer to the associated Assembly Procedure
               document TRI67.006 for

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yd0 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               detailed procedures on making the cell sense wiring
               harness.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha yd1 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               5.8.1Temperature Sensor

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yd2 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The recommended cell temperature sensor to use is a
               Murata 10k NTC bead type

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yd3 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               thermistor (NXFT15XH103FA2B100) with 100mm leads. The
               thermistor should be

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yd4 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               attached to a part of the cell that is a good
               representation of the internal

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y42 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               temperature, such as a cell terminal (Care MUST be taken
               that the sensor is

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yaa ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               appropriately insulated from the terminal).

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha yd5 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               6 CMU CAN BUS

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yd6 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The CMUs and BMU communicate via CAN bus at a fixed
               125kbit/s rate, running

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yd7 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               over standard 1.27mm pitch 10-way IDC ribbon cable.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yd8 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMU supplies 12V power to the CMUs along this cable.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yd9 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               As a CAN bus, this cable requires termination of the
               CAN-H and CAN-L signals

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yda ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               together at both ends of the network. Use the supplied
               CMU CAN termination

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ydb ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               boards to do this.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ydc ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Use a single length of cable to join all CMUs, the BMU,
               and both termination

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ydd ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               resistors together. This can easily be achieved by
               crimping on a standard 10-way

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yde ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               IDC crimp as the cable passes each device.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ydf ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Pin 1 on each device is indicated by an arrow and the
               numeral '1' on the PCB,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ye0 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               and/or an arrow moulded in the connector.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ye1 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Make sure that the ribbon is oriented correctly on all
               devices: Pin 1 should join to

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ye2 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Pin 1 on every other device, and should also be the
               polarity indication on the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ye3 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               ribbon cable, usually a red stripe.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ye4 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The CMU CAN bus cable is electrically connected to
               vehicle ground at the BMU,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ye5 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               and therefore must be kept physically separated from any
               battery or other HV

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ye6 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               connections to at least the maximum voltage rating of the
               pack.

            .. container:: t m0 x6 h8 yc ff2 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               9 of 29

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y9a ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               7.1FORM FACTOR

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y9b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMS Master Unit (BMU) is supplied as a 1.6mm
               thickness Printed Circuit

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y9c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Board (PCB), conformally coated, without an enclosure. It
               is designed to be

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y9d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               installed inside the battery box, in a weather-sealed
               area, along with the cells

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y9e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               themselves. This means that all connections to the pack
               remain inside the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y9f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               battery pack enclosure, simplifying fusing and wiring
               installation requirements.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yed ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMU should be mounted to a flat surface, using 7x M3
               standoffs, of sufficient

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yee ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               length to allow the appropriate clearance distance
               between the components on

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yef ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the PCB and the mounting surface. Use of an insulation
               material layer may allow

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yf0 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               a lower-profile mounting. This distance will be
               determined by the maximum

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yf1 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               operating voltage of the pack, required isolation voltage
               rating, and regulatory

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yf2 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               creepage and clearance distances.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yf3 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               All connections to the BMU are along one edge,
               simplifying wire routing inside

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yf4 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               your battery enclosure. Wiring should be appropriately
               strain relieved to

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yf5 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               withstand the vibration typically found in an automotive
               environment – do not

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yf6 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               support the weight of the wiring loom solely from the
               connectors on the BMU.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha yf7 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               7.3CONNECTORS OVERVIEW

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yae ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The following illustration shows the connections on the
               BMU:

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yf9 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Refer to the relevant sections of this document for more
               details on the pinout and

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yfa ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               wiring for each connector.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha yfb ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               7.4ISOLATION

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yfc ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The HV Sense connection is isolated from the remainder of
               the BMU with an

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yfd ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               isolation barrier rated for 1000V DC. This allows the HV
               battery pack to be fully

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yfe ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               floating from the vehicle chassis, as is required by most
               EV construction

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yff ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               standards (eg NCOP14 in Australia).

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y100 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The remainder of the BMU operates relative to the GND
               supplied along the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y101 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               vehicle CAN bus connection, and this must be tied to the
               vehicle chassis at some

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y102 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               point in the system.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y103 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               7.5INDICATORS

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y104 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The output status of the three contactor drives, fan
               outputs, and CMU CAN bus

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y105 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               power are all indicated with green LEDs at the edge of
               the BMU adjacent to the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y106 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               relevant connector.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y107 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Other indications and faults can be observed using the
               Windows PC software via

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y108 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the CAN-Ethernet bridge, or by any other device on the
               CAN bus that is

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y109 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               programmed to receive status messages from the BMS.

               8 HV SENSE

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The HV Sense connector allows the BMU to measure the
               total pack voltage (pack

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               side of the contactors), total DC bus voltage (vehicle
               side of the contactors), and

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y82 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               total pack current flow. This information is used to
               control precharge and pack

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y83 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               safety, and to calculate pack Ah usage and SOC.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The HV Sense connector and associated electronics are
               isolated from the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               remainder of the BMU. Take care when routing wiring
               around this connector to

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y84 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               maintain good isolation between it and the rest of the
               vehicle system.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y61 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Wire the Vehicle HV+ and Battery HV+ sense wires to their
               respective sides of

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y62 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Contactor 2 in the positive rail. Wire the Battery HV–
               and Shunt sense wires to

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y63 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               their respective sides of the current shunt in the
               negative rail. Refer to the BMS

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y118 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               wiring diagram in the Appendix for more details.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y119 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Please note that this sense wiring must be rated for the
               full pack voltage,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y11a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               although it is low current so a small gauge wire can be
               used. Check the relevant

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y11b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               wiring standards regarding wire rating and colours, for
               example NCOP14 (in

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y11c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Australia) specifies Orange wire for all battery pack and
               other HV system wiring.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y11d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The Battery HV– and Shunt sense wires should be twisted
               together to minimise

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y11e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               noise pickup between the BMU and the shunt. It is
               suggested to have these wires

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y11f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               no longer than 300-400mm.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y120 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               8.1HV SENSE CONNECTOR

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y121 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The connector used for the HV Sense is a 10-way 4.2mm
               pitch Molex MiniFit Jr

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y122 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               connector. The pinout is shown below, as viewed from the
               wire side – as you

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y123 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               would look at it while inserting crimps. The colours
               shown match those

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y124 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               recommended in most EV wiring standards for HV DC wiring.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y125 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The sense points are as follows:

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y126 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y127 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               8.2HV SENSE FUSING

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yae ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               All HV Sense connections should be fused with an
               appropriately rated fuse for the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ycc ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               type of wire used for the sense connection. This fuse
               should be low current

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ycd ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               (since the sense wiring uses small wires) and rated for
               the full DC pack voltage.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yce ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The fuse should be located towards the supply end of the
               sense wiring.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y136 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               9 PACK CURRENT SENSE

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y137 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMU provides a mechanism for measuring pack current
               using a resistive

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y138 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               shunt. This is preferred over hall-effect based sensors
               as it provides much lower

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y139 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               drift, allowing more accurate State of Charge (SOC)
               integration calculation.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y13a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The shunt must be located in the Battery HV– connection
               of the pack, as shown

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y13b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               in the BMS wiring diagram in the Appendix.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y13c ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               9.1SHUNT SELECTION

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y13d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMU Shunt Sense input has a full-scale range of
               ±25mV, relative to the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y13e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Battery HV– Sense input. This allows the use of a
               standard 50mV shunt running

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y13f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               at half its rated current to minimise heat buildup and
               thermal drift effects, since it

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y11d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               will be installed inside the battery pack.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y140 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Choose a full-scale range slightly over the expected
               maximum battery current.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y141 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               As an example, a Tritium WaveSculptor200 motor controller
               driving an induction

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y142 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               motor may have an expected maximum power consumption of
               90kW. At a 400V

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y143 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               battery voltage, this is 225A. Choose a full scale of
               250A to allow some

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y144 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               headroom on the measurement. Since we wish to use a
               standard 50mV shunt at

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y145 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               half rating, you would therefore select a 500A/50mV
               shunt.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y146 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The value of the shunt can be set in the user-interface
               software.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y147 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               9.2STATE OF CHARGE REPORTING

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y148 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMU takes readings of the shunt current using a
               high-accuracy front-end

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y149 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               circuit and 24-bit A/D converter. It integrates these
               readings to accumulate an

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y14a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Ah consumption for the pack.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y14b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The Ah accumulation is used in conjunction with the
               user-settable pack capacity

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y14c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               value to calculate a SOC in percent. Both Ah and percent
               are reported on the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y14d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               CAN bus.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y14e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The SOC reading is reset to 'full' when the first bypass
               shunt has activated during

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y14f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               a charge cycle. At this point the “Balance SOC” telemetry
               value begins

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y150 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               incrementing, halting when all bypass shunts are active.
               This “Balance SOC”

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y151 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               telemetry value therefore shows the amount of imbalance
               between cells that has

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y152 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               been corrected during the current charging session.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y153 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               9.3OVERCURRENT SHUTDOWN

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y154 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMU has the capability to shut down the pack by
               opening the contactors if

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y155 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the pack current exceeds a fixed threshold. This function
               is not currently

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y156 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               implemented in the default firmware, but will be added at
               a later date.

            .. container:: t m0 x2c h8 yc ff2 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               10 CONTACTOR DRIVE / SENSE

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMU provides three outputs for driving HV contactors
               with 12V coils. At a

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               minimum Contactors 1 & 2 are required for pack safety,
               although this option still

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y82 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               presents a shock hazard (via the precharge resistor) in a
               single-fault situation to

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y83 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the rest of the system. A professional design will use
               all three contactors.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The contactors are energised in sequence (1, 3, 2) during
               precharge, and de-

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               energised when shutting down the system both under user
               command and due to

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y84 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               a fault being detected by the BMS. The BMU operates the
               contactors to protect

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y85 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the cells above all other priorities.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y62 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Each contactor output connector also has pins for
               feedback from contactors with

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y63 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               auxilliary sense contacts. These can be used by the BMU
               to detect failed

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y118 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               contactors, both failed open or welded shut. Do not
               connect these pins to

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y89 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               anything other than auxilliary contact output terminals –
               they are not rated for

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y8a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               anything more than the 12V supplied by the BMU.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y11b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Refer to the BMS datasheet for continuous and peak
               current and voltage ratings

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y11c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               of the contactor drive outputs. Contactors without
               integrated electronics must

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y158 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               have a diode fitted across their coil terminals to limit
               flyback voltage at turn-off. 

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y159 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               10.1CONTACTOR 12V SUPPLY CONNECTOR

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y15a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The connector used for the Contactor 12V supply input is
               a 2-way 4.2mm pitch

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y15b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Molex MiniFit Jr connector. The pinout is shown below, as
               viewed from the wire

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y15c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               side – as you would look at it while inserting crimps.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y15d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               This connection should be wired to the vehicle 12V DC
               supply via the emergency

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y15e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               stop switch (if fitted), the G-force impact switch, an
               optional HV disable switch,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y15f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               and a fuse. It requires a low impedance connection to the
               vehicle battery, since

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y160 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               most contactors draw a large current inrush during
               turn-on, and a poor

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y161 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               connection will result in contactor chattering and/or
               precharge fault trips.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y162 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               This connection draws no current when the BMS is in the
               off state, and does not

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y57 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               have to be routed via the ignition key. Connecting it to
               a permanent source of

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y163 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               power (rather than via the ignition key) allows the BMS
               to operate the contactors

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y164 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               without the ignition key switched on, for example during
               charging.

            .. container:: t m0 x2c h8 yc ff2 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               11 PRECHARGE

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y16f ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               11.1CONCEPT

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y170 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Loads such as motor controllers (inverters), DC/DC
               converters, and other high-

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y171 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               voltage, high-power electronics contain capacitors across
               the DC bus. If these

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y172 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               are suddenly connected to the battery pack by closing a
               contactor or switch, then

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y173 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               there will be a very large inrush current (thousands of
               Amps) followed by a

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y174 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               voltage surge due to the battery and cabling inductance.
               This inrush current will

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y175 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               damage the devices and weld contacts together, and the
               voltage surge can also

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y176 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               cause components to fail.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y177 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Precharging the capacitors in the various devices solves
               these problems. This

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y178 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               can be done by first connecting the loads to the battery
               through a resistor, so

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y179 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               that the current into the capacitors is limited to a few
               amps. The voltage on the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y17a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               capacitors will then rise in a controlled manner, and
               when it is close to the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y17b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               battery voltage the main contactor can be closed to
               directly connect everything

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y17c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               together.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y17d ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               11.2ACTION

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y17e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMU initiates a precharge sequence when commanded to
               do so from the EV

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y17f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Driver Controls. There are two conditions that begin
               precharge: the ignition key

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y180 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               moving to the start position from the run position; and
               the fuel door being

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y181 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               opened for charging.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y182 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Either closing the fuel door, or moving the key to no
               longer be in Ignition run

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y183 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               position will shut down the system and open the
               contactors to make the system

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y184 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               safe.

            .. container:: t m0 x2c h8 yc ff2 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               15 of 29

            .. container:: t m0 x4d h23 y10f ff2 fse fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

      .. container:: pc pc10 w0 h0

         |image15|

         .. container:: c x1 y1 w0 h2

            .. container:: t m0 x2 h3 y2 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               USER'S MANUAL

            .. container:: t m0 x3 h4 y3 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Battery Management System

            .. container:: t m0 x4 h5 y4 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               TRI67.011 ver 3

            .. container:: t m0 x4 h5 y5 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               31 August 2015

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y34 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMU can also be set to run in “Standalone Operation”
               mode, where it will

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y18c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               precharge as soon as it measures an acceptable voltage on
               the 12V contactor

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y18d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               power input. This mode would normally be used in remote
               area power

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y18e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               installations and similar applications, not in vehicles.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y18f ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               11.3SEQUENCE

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y190 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The precharge sequence is as follows:

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y191 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               1.Contactor 1 energises to connect Pack- to the vehicle

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y60 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               2.Contactor 3 energises to connect Pack+ to the precharge
               resistor, and

            .. container:: t m0 x4e h4 y192 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               allow the BMU to take pack voltage measurements. A pack
               isolation test is

            .. container:: t m0 x4e h4 y62 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               performed at this point

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y193 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               3.The capacitors in the devices in the vehicle precharge
               through the

            .. container:: t m0 x4e h4 y194 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               precharge resistor that is in parallel with Contactor 2

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y195 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               4.When the pack voltage and the DC bus voltage are within
               tolerance then

            .. container:: t m0 x4e h4 y13d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Contactor 2 is energised to complete the high-current
               circuit

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y196 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               5.The BMU is now in “Run” mode, and does the following:

            .. container:: t m0 x4e h4 y197 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •reports this fact on the CAN bus

            .. container:: t m0 x4e h4 y198 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •activates the status relay output (which can be used to
               enable the

            .. container:: t m0 x32 h4 y199 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               DC/DC converter)

            .. container:: t m0 x4e h4 y19a ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •turns on the pack fan outputs

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y19b ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               11.4PRECHARGE RESISTOR SELECTION

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y19c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Selection of the external precharge resistor is critical
               for correct and long-term

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y19d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               reliable operation of the precharge circuit. A judgement
               must be made by the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y19e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               designer of the vehicle power system to the tradeoff
               between resistor size, cost

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y19f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               and weight, and expected precharge time. A slower time
               can use a smaller,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1a0 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               cheaper resistor, but taking too long to precharge will
               be annoying to the end

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1a1 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               user of the vehicle. An aluminium-cased wirewound
               resistor is the most

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1a2 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               commonly chosen type of resistor.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1a3 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               As an example, the calculations for a typical EV system
               are shown as follows:

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1a4 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               System battery voltage maximum = 450V

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1a5 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Motor controller (Tritium Wavesculptor 200) capacitance =
               800µF

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1a6 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Chosen precharge current = 1A

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1a7 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Therefore, the minimum resistance (fastest precharge)
               will be 450V / 1A = 450

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1a8 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Ohms. Choose 470 Ohms as the next highest common value.
               Peak power

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1a9 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               dissipation in the resistor is therefore 450V²/470R =
               430W.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1aa ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The expected precharge time is given by the time constant
               TAU = R (Ohms) \* C

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1ab ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               (Farads), where the voltage on the capacitor should
               change by 63% of the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1ac ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               difference each TAU time interval. Precharge should be
               within 95% of the initial

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1ad ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               value within 4 TAU, and to 99% within 5 TAU intervals, as
               an exponential decay.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1ae ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               For the example system, TAU = 376ms, so the expected
               precharge time of 4 TAU

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1af ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               = 1.5 seconds.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1b0 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Choosing a >500W resistor is unnecessary, as this rating
               is only needed for a

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1b1 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               short amount of time during normal operation. However,
               the resistor cannot be

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1b2 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               too small, as if a fault situation occurs, such as a
               short circuit in the motor

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1b3 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               controller, then this power will be dissipated
               continuously for the entire expected

            .. container:: t m0 x2c h8 yc ff2 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               16 of 29

   .. container:: pf w0 h0

      .. container:: pc pc11 w0 h0

         |image16|

         .. container:: c x1 y1 w0 h2

            .. container:: t m0 x2 h3 y2 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               USER'S MANUAL

            .. container:: t m0 x3 h4 y3 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Battery Management System

            .. container:: t m0 x4 h5 y4 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               TRI67.011 ver 3

            .. container:: t m0 x4 h5 y5 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               31 August 2015

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y34 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               precharge time, until the precharge controller realises
               that precharging has not

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y18c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               occurred properly and goes into an error state. For
               safety, the resistor in the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y18d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               example system should be chosen to tolerate a one-off
               event, starting at the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y18e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               expected maximum ambient temperature, of 430W for 1.5
               seconds.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1b5 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Searching through available off-the-shelf options from
               Digikey, the RH series from

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1b6 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Vishay is chosen as a likely candidate. According to the
               datasheet located at

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1b7 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               http://www.vishay.com/docs/50013/rh.pdf , for short time
               overloads, a power

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1b8 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               rating of 12x the nominal power is acceptable for a 2
               second duration. Using a

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1b9 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               50W resistor, this equates to an overload rating of 600W,
               starting at an ambient

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1ba ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               of 25°C.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1bb ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Therefore, this 50W resistor is acceptable for the
               external resistor in this

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1bc ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               application based on maximum fault power.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1bd ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               During normal operation, the capacitors contain a charge
               of 0.36C, giving an

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1be ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               energy storage of 81 Joules. Note that this is a lethal
               amount of energy. During

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1bf ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               an RC precharge type event, the same amount of energy
               that is eventually

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1c0 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               stored in the capacitor is also dissipated in the
               resistor.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1c1 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               If not mounted on any additional thermal mass, and
               assuming that 20g of the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1c2 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               resistor's total mass is aluminium (specific heat = 0.897
               J/g°C), 81 Joules will give

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1c3 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               a temperature rise of ∆T = Q/mc = 4.5°C, also well within
               limits. During a fault

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1c4 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               situation, where 430W is being dissipated in the
               resistor, the same thermal

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1c5 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               calculation shows a temperature rise of 48°C above the
               starting temperature.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1c6 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               This also is within limits.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1c7 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The maximum acceptable operating voltage for the 50W
               resistor is 1285V, so our

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1c8 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               maximum of 450V is also within limits.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1c9 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Therefore, a 470 ohm, 50W, RH series wirewound aluminium
               resistor

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1ca ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               would be a suitable choice of external resistor for this
               application of precharging

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1cb ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               800uF to 450V in 1.5 seconds. Other devices on the HV bus
               such as DC/DC

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1cc ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               converters and battery chargers will add significant
               extra capacitance, and must

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1cd ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               be factored into these calculations.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1ce ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Note that the BMS must be programmed with the correct
               timeout value, so as it

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1cf ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               knows what the expected precharge time is. If this is not
               done, then the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1d0 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               precharge controller will either expect precharge to have
               finished when it has

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1d1 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               not, resulting in an error state, or it will expect
               precharge to take much longer

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1d2 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               than it really does, resulting in a potential overload
               and a fire in the external

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1d3 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               resistor if there is a system fault.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y1d4 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               11.5CAVEATS

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1d5 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Be aware that loads that draw current during precharge
               will cause the precharge

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1d6 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               sequence to fail and/or the precharge resistor to
               overheat. This is because the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1d7 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               current drawn by the load will slow or possibly prevent
               the output voltage from

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1d8 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               rising, meaning precharge never completes in the expected
               time.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1d9 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The typical load that causes this problem is the DC/DC
               converter used to charge

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1da ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the 12V auxilliary battery.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1db ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               This problem can be avoided by using the relay output on
               the BMU to control an

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1dc ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               “enable” input on the problematic loads once precharge
               has completed and the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1dd ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               BMU is in “Run” mode. By default, this relay activates in
               this manner.

            .. container:: t m0 x2c h8 yc ff2 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

            .. container:: t m0 x2 h3 y2 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               USER'S MANUAL

            .. container:: t m0 x3 h4 y3 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Battery Management System

            .. container:: t m0 x4 h5 y4 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               TRI67.011 ver 3

            .. container:: t m0 x4 h5 y5 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               31 August 2015

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha ye ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               12 TRUSTED MEASUREMENTS

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The CMUs measure their cell voltages using two separate
               front-end circuits, A/D

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               converters, and voltage references. One channel records
               with a high resolution

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y82 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               24-bit converter at a slow 2 Hz rate. The other channel
               uses a mid resolution 12-

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y83 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               bit converter running at several kHz. These are
               cross-checked against each other

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y190 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               to verify that the CMU is functioning correctly and that
               the cell voltage

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1df ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               measurement can be trusted.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y84 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Measurements reported on the CAN bus telemetry come from
               the high resolution

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y85 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               channel.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y62 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Measurements where the two channels do not agree are
               flagged as untrusted. If

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y63 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               any cells report an untrusted measurement, the BMU will
               report a TRUST error on

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y118 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the CAN bus. This is not treated as a fatal error, and
               will not result in a pack

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y89 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               shutdown.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y11a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The threshold where a trust error is generated is set in
               the BMU config, and is

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y11b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               currently factory set to 100mV.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y13f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Please note that due to the different response rates of
               the two A/D converters, it

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y11d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               is possible to get a trust error briefly during sharp
               voltage transients on the cells,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y11e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               for instance during rapid acceleration or regen braking
               events. Whatever higher-

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y11f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               level vehicle system is handling BMS telemetry and user
               interface should be

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1e0 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               programmed to ignore trust errors that are present for
               less than some period (eg

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1e1 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               500ms) of time.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y1e2 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               13 FUSING

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1e3 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The battery pack must be fused in each physical pack
               section with a fuse rated

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1e4 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               for at least the full DC pack voltage. Note that it must
               be a DC rated fuse.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1e5 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Selection of fuse type and current rating is beyond the
               scope of this document,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1e6 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               as it depends on expected load profile and duration,
               cable sizing and

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1e7 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               temperature rating, cable installation methods, and
               short-circuit rating of the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1e8 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               pack, among other factors.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y1e9 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               14 CONTACTOR SELECTION

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1ea ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The three contactors used to break the HV DC connections
               must be appropriately

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1eb ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               rated for the currents and voltages seen during both
               normal use and during fault

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1ec ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               situations. Typical parts used in automotive sized packs
               are the Tyco EV200 or

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1ed ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the Gigavac GX11 or GX12 series. Selection of these parts
               is beyond the scope of

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1ee ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               this document.

            .. container:: t m0 x2c h8 yc ff2 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

            .. container:: t m0 x2 h3 y2 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               USER'S MANUAL

            .. container:: t m0 x3 h4 y3 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Battery Management System

            .. container:: t m0 x4 h5 y4 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               TRI67.011 ver 3

            .. container:: t m0 x4 h5 y5 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               31 August 2015

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha ye ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               15 OPERATING THRESHOLDS

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               There are six user-settable thresholds that control the
               operation of the BMS.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               These should be set based on the maximum acceptable
               limits for the cells used

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y82 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               in the battery pack, along with reference to the
               charge/discharge curves for

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y83 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               selecting the balancing points.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               These operating points can be programmed into the BMU
               over the CAN bus using

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the BMS Setup software and a Tritium CAN-Ethernet bridge.
               Settings that are

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y84 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               required at the CMUs are passed to them from the BMU when
               the system starts.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y61 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The SOC vs Voltage curve for a typical Lithium chemistry
               cell is shown below,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y62 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               along with the location of the various thresholds.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y1f0 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               15.1OVER VOLTAGE THRESHOLD

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1f1 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               This voltage should be set to the maximum acceptable
               voltage for the cell. If it is

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1f2 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               ever exceeded, then the BMS will move to the Error state
               and open the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1f3 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               contactors immediately to protect the pack.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y1f4 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               15.2BALANCE THRESHOLD

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y150 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               This voltage is the target setpoint for the charging
               control algorithm, and will be

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1f5 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the voltage that the cells are charged to in normal
               operation. It should be chosen

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y152 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               to be part-way up the 'knee' in the voltage charge curve,
               so that the cells can be

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1f6 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               easily seen to be at different SOC and therefore balanced
               accurately.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1f7 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Choosing this number to be higher (closer towards the
               Over Voltage Threshold)

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1f8 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               will give a slightly increased useable capacity of the
               pack, but will make it more

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1f9 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               likely that sudden regen braking will push a cell above
               the Over Voltage

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1fa ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Threshold and shut down the system without warning.
               Pushing the usual charge

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1fb ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               voltage to the maximum rating of the cell may also reduce
               cell cycle life – refer to

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1fc ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the cell datasheet for specific information on this
               aspect, as it is highly

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1fd ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y34 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Threshold by the Balance Threshold Hysteresis value.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y208 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               15.3BALANCE THRESHOLD HYSTERESIS

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y209 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               This voltage determines the hysteresis used to control
               the balance resistors.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               If using CMUs made after January 2013, it should be set
               to around 5mV, as the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y20a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               firmware in the newer CMUs turns off the shunt resistors
               while taking voltage

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y5e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               measurements to eliminate errors caused by the resistance
               of the sense wiring.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y20b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               If using older CMUs, it should be set to around 50mV for
               a typical pack, to allow

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y60 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               for the voltage drop in the sense wiring, connections,
               and cell impedance when

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y192 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               250mA of balance current is flowing. This will be
               installation dependent.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y20c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Setting it too low will cause oscillations in the balance
               resistor switching and

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y193 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               possibly erroneous voltage measurement reporting.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y20d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Setting it too high will give a wide band of voltage that
               various cells are balanced

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y195 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               to, giving a less than optimally balanced pack and
               slightly reduced pack capacity.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y20e ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               15.4ZERO SOC THRESHOLD

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y20f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               This voltage should be set to the point where the cells
               are considered fully

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y210 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               discharged during normal operation. It will be along the
               lower 'knee' in the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y211 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               charge curve. When a cell goes below this threshold, the
               BMU reports SOC as

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y212 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               0%. It is also the target minimum voltage used by motor
               controllers and other

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y213 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               devices to not exceed during operation.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y214 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               15.5UNDER VOLTAGE THRESHOLD

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y215 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               This voltage should be set to the minimum acceptable
               voltage for the cell. If any

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y216 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               cell voltage falls below this point, then the BMS will
               move to the Error state and

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y217 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               open the contactors immediately to protect the pack.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y218 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               15.6OVER TEMPERATURE THRESHOLD

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y219 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               This temperature should be set to the maximum acceptable
               operating

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y21a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               temperature for the cell. If it is ever exceeded, then
               the BMS will move to the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y21b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Error state and open the contactors immediately to
               protect the pack.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y21c ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               16 CHARGER CONTROL

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y175 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               To charge and balance the pack correctly the BMS must be
               able to control the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y21d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               charging current in a continuous manner. Therefore, a
               charger that is able to be

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y21e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               controlled remotely is required. Battery management
               systems and chargers that

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y4f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               use on/off control will result in slow and/or poor
               balancing of cells.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y179 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Suitable chargers that the BMS currently supports are the
               Brusa NLG series, and

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y21f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the TC Charger range with CAN-bus option. Please contact
               Tritium regarding

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y17b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               support for other types of chargers.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y220 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMU runs a PID control loop based on maximum
               individual cell voltage, with

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y221 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the aim of raising it up to the Balance Thresholdvoltage.
               It will issue current

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y222 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               setpoint commands to the charger to achieve this goal.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y223 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               This control strategy results in the minimum possible
               charge time, as the charger

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y224 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               will be ramped up to maximum current rapidly, and stay
               there until the maximum

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y225 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               cell reaches the target voltage at the end of the
               'constant current' portion of the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y226 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               charge cycle. At this point, charge current will be
               gradually ramped down, at

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y227 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               whatever rate is necessary to keep the maximum cell at
               the target and adsorbing

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y12f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               as quickly as possible – the 'constant voltage' portion
               of the charge cycle.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y228 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Therefore, it does not matter at what rate the cell is
               adsorbing charge, the

            .. container:: t m0 x2c h8 yc ff2 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0
