               USER'S MANUAL

            .. container:: t m0 x3 h4 y3 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Battery Management System

            .. container:: t m0 x4 h5 y4 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               TRI67.011 ver 3

            .. container:: t m0 x4 h5 y5 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               31 August 2015

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y34 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               control loop will keep it at the optimal amount at all
               times.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y22a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               As the maximum cell reaches 100% SOC, the charging
               current will have been

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y22b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               gradually reduced down until it matches the balance
               current of ~250mA. At this

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y22c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               point, the maximum cell will be at the target voltage,
               held at that point by the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1b5 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               balance resistor, and lower cells in the pack will be
               rising at the rate governed by

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1b6 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the 250mA charge.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y22d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               When the minimum cell reaches the target voltage, then
               all cells are in balance,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y22e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               and the pack is at 100% SOC. This time difference between
               maximum and

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y22f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               minimum cells reaching the target voltage is usually only
               a few minutes for a

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y230 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               well-balanced battery pack. Therefore, the power wasted
               in the balance resistors

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1bb ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               during this time is a trivial percentage of the total
               charge energy.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y231 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Note that the very first balance may take considerable
               time if the cells are

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1bd ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               grossly out of balance. Worst-case time is the Ah
               capacity of the cells divided by

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1be ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the 250mA balance rate divided by the out-of-balance
               percentage, eg 90Ah /

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1bf ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               0.25A / 20% = 72 hours.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y232 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               17 OPERATING STATE

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y233 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMS can be in any one of six states, depending on
               operating conditions,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y234 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               commands, and errors. The states are reported on the CAN
               bus, and shown in

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y235 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the BMS Viewer software. The states are, in the most
               commonly seen sequence:

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y236 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Error

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y237 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Idle

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y238 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Enable

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y239 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Measure

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y23a ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Precharge

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y23b ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Run

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y23c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               States transition from one to another based on various
               thresholds and timers,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y23d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               and on user commands from the Tritium EV Driver Controls
               via the CAN bus, as

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y23e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               detailed in the following sections.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y23f ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               17.1ERROR

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y240 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMS is in the Error state if any of the following
               conditions are true:

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y241 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •The 12V contactor supply is not present or is
               undervoltage

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y242 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Any cell Over Voltage

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y243 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Any cell Under Voltage

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y244 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Any cell Over Temperature

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y245 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Any CMU communications packet is overdue (CMU timeout)

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y246 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Packets from the EV driver controls are overdue (vehicle
               timeout)

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y247 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Missing CMU or cell

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y248 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Extra CMU or cell

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y249 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Contactor feedback mismatch to the commanded state of
               the contactor

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y24a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               In the Error state, all contactors are switched off to
               isolate the pack. The relay

            .. container:: t m0 x2c h8 yc ff2 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

            .. container:: t m0 x2 h3 y2 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               USER'S MANUAL

            .. container:: t m0 x3 h4 y3 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Battery Management System

            .. container:: t m0 x4 h5 y4 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

            .. container:: t m0 x4 h5 y5 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y34 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               and fan outputs are also switched off.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y22a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               If all errors are removed, then the BMS will transition
               to the Idle state if the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y22b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               ignition key is switched to the accessories position and
               the fuel dooris closed. It

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y22c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               requires this active user intervention to move to Idle,
               and will otherwise remain in

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y1b5 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the Error state.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y24b ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               17.2IDLE

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y191 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               In the Idle state, the BMS waits for a command from the
               EV driver controls. All

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y84 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               contactors are switched off. The relay output and fans
               are also off.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y192 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               If the ignition key is switched from the runposition to
               thestartposition, or the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y62 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               fuel dooris opened, then the BMS transitions to the
               Enable state and begins a

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y24c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               precharge sequence.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y24d ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               17.3ENABLE

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y24e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Contactor 1 is switched on, to connect the Pack-
               connection to the vehicle. After

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y24f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               a short time to allow the inrush current from the
               contactor switching to subside

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y250 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               on the 12V supply, the BMS transitions to the Measure
               state.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y251 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               17.4MEASURE

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y252 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Contactor 3 is also switched on, to connect the Pack+
               connection to the vehicle

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y253 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               via the precharge resistor. The vehicle will begin
               precharging.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y254 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The pack isolation test is run during this interval

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y255 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               After a short time to allow the total pack voltage
               measurement to stabilise, and

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y215 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the 12V current inrush from the contactor switching to
               subside, the BMS

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y216 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               transitions to the Precharge state.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y256 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               17.5PRECHARGE

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y257 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The load will now be precharging. The BMS begins a
               timeout (error) counter

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y219 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               (2000ms by default), to avoid a fault situation
               overheating the precharge resistor,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y21a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               and also begins comparing the total pack voltage and DC
               bus voltage

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y21b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               measurements.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y258 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               When they match within a the precharge voltage threshold
               (20V by default),

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y259 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               precharge is regarded as complete and the BMS transitions
               to the Run state.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y25a ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               17.6RUN

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y25b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Contactor 2 is also switched on, to directly connect the
               Pack+ connection to the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y25c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               load. The relay and fan outputs are switched on.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y25d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               If the ignition key is switched away from the run
               position (back to accessories) or

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y25e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the fuel door is closed, then the BMS transitions to the
               Idle state.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y25f ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               18 STATE OF CHARGE (SOC) REPORTING

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y260 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMS reports State of Charge (SOC) based on
               integrating the pack current

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y261 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               (coulomb counting).

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y262 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The SOC is calculated in Amp-Hours (Ah), based on the
               user-set scale value for

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y263 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the 25mV shunt. The Ah is then also calculated to a
               percentage, based on the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y264 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               user-set value for total pack capacity.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y265 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Ah are set to zero when the first cell reaches the
               balance threshold while

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y266 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               charging for the first time. It then counts up to
               indicate Ah drawn from the pack.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y267 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               It will count back down towards zero when the pack is
               recharged.

            .. container:: t m0 x2c h8 yc ff2 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               19 PACK ISOLATION DETECTION

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y26d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMU contains hardware that is capable of sensing if
               the HV battery pack

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y26e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               connections (both + and –, and any point along the pack)
               are isolated from the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y26f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               chassis. This test is run during each startup sequence,
               and a failed test will

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y270 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               report as an isolation fault in the configuration
               software.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y271 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               A failed pack isolation test will not prevent operation
               of the system, but should be

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y272 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               flagged by the user interface for the system (eg
               dashboard display) and indicate

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y273 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               to the user to seek servicing.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y274 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               20 FAN/PUMP CONTROL

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y275 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMU provides two 12V switched outputs to drive pack
               fans and pumps.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y276 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               These are provided on a standard 3-pin KK connector as
               used in PCs and other IT

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y277 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               equipment. Both outputs are switched together, ie both on
               or both off.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y278 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The 12V to power these outputs is sourced from the
               contactor supply input

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y279 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               connection.Refer to the datasheet for current and voltage
               ratings for these

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y27a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               outputs.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y27b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Both connections provide a speed sensor input pin, and
               this is measured by the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y27c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               BMU and reported as an rpm number for each connection on
               the CAN bus

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y27d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               telemetry. It assumes a 2 pulse per revolution sensor
               output, as is commonly

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y27e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               used for most PC cooling fans.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y27f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMS firmware switches both outputs on when the BMS is
               in Run mode (once

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y280 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               precharge has completed and the system is fully
               operational).

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y281 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               20.1FAN/PUMP CONNECTORS

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y282 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The connector used for the pump/fan outputs is a 3-way
               2.54mm pitch Molex KK

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y283 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               connector. The pinout is shown below, as viewed from the
               wire side – as you

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y284 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               would look at it while inserting crimps.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y285 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The pinout follows the standard used for PC cooling fans
               and pumps, as found on

            .. container:: t m0 x2c h8 yc ff2 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               23 of 29

               21 RELAY OUTPUT

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y28b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMU provides a voltage-free relay output to use for
               signalling devices in the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y28c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               vehicle that are not capable of receiving CAN bus data.
               This can be used, for

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y28d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               example, to control the 'enable' input of a DC/DC
               converter or drive a relay or HV

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y3a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               contactor. A coil suppression diode must be used if
               driving this type of load.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y28e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Refer to the datasheet for current and voltage ratings of
               the relay.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y28f ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The relay is active when the BMS is in Run mode.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y290 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The connector also provides 12V and GND pins, which are
               sourced from the 12V

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y291 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               contactor supply power. These can be conveniently used in
               conjunction with the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y292 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               relay to switch 12V out to a load that requires power,
               for instance to drive

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y293 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               another relay, fan or contactor.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y294 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               21.1RELAY OUTPUT CONNECTOR

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y295 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The connector used for the Relay output is a 6-way 4.2mm
               pitch Molex MiniFit Jr

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y296 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               connector. The pinout is shown below, as viewed from the
               wire side – as you

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y297 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               would look at it while inserting crimps.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y298 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The +12V and Ground pins in this connector are wired (on
               the BMU PCB) to the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y299 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Contactor 12V supply connector, and can be jumpered
               across to the relay pins to

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y29a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               provide 12V output on relay active or inactive, switch
               loads to ground, etc,

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y29b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               depending on the jumper arrangement.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y29c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The Relay pins in this connector are wired directly to a
               small relay on the BMU

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y29d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               PCB. Refer to the datasheet for the ratings on this
               relay.

               22 VEHICLE CAN BUS

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y9a ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               22.1CAN NETWORK TOPOLOGY

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y9b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The CAN bus is structured as a linear network, with short
               stubs branching from 'T'

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y9c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               connectors on the main bus backbone to each device. The
               CAN bus data lines

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y9d ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               must be terminated at each end of the main bus with 120
               ohm resistors between

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y9e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the CAN-H and CAN-L signals.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2a3 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               In the range of Tritium EV products, including the
               WaveSculptor 200, EV Driver

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yed ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Controls, and BMU, the CAN connections are implemented
               with an 'in' and an

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yee ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               'out' connector, therefore placing the 'T' on the device,
               resulting in a very short

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yef ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               fixed-length stub on the circuit board of each device.
               This is ideal from a signal

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 yf0 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               integrity and network performance point of view.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2a4 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMU uses the vehicle CAN bus to receive operating and
               configuration

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2a5 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               commands and transmit telemetry, as well as a source of
               low-voltage DC power

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2a6 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               to operate the electronics.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y2a7 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               22.2CAN WIRING

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2a8 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The CAN data lines (CAN-H and CAN-L) must be implemented
               with twisted-pair

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2a9 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               wire for proper data integrity. The wire should have a
               characteristic impedance

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2aa ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               of 120 ohms. 

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2ab ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Power should also be provided along the CAN cable,
               ideally with another twisted

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2ac ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               pair to minimise noise pickup. An overall shield can also
               be advantageous.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2ad ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The optimal choice of cable is 7mm Devicenet CANbus
               'thin' cable, with 24AWG

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2ae ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               (data) + 22AWG (power) twisted pairs and a braided
               shield. Using this cable will

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2af ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               result in a robust installation, with high immunity to
               noise, low voltage drop in the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2b0 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               power cable, and reliable CAN communications. Using
               alternative cabling will

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2b1 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               usually result in problems during operation.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y2b2 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               22.3VEHICLE CAN BUS CONNECTORS

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2b3 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The connector used on the BMU and other Tritium devices
               for the CAN connection

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2b4 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               is a 6-way 3mm pitch Molex MicroFit connector. The pinout
               is shown below, as

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2b5 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               viewed from the wire side – as you would look at it while
               inserting crimps. The

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2b6 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               colours shown match those in the standard DeviceNet CAN
               cabling pairs.

            .. container:: t m0 x2c h8 yc ff2 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               25 of 29

               22.4CAN SHIELDING

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2b8 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               If the recommended braided shield is used in the cable,
               then terminate it to the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2b9 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               SHIELD pin (lower-left corner on the connector) on both
               CAN IN and CAN OUT

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2ba ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               connectors on each device.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2bb ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               On one device onlyin the network, instead of using the
               SHIELD pin, terminate

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2bc ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               the shield to the SHIELD GROUND pin (upper-left corner on
               the connector) on

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2bd ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               both CAN IN and CAN OUT connectors, to ground the shield
               for the entire network

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2be ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               at this single point. The usual place to do this is where
               power is fed into the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2bf ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               network, typically at Tritium's EV Driver
               Controlsproduct.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y2c0 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               22.5CAN TERMINATION

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y201 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               To implement the required 120 Ohm termination resistor at
               each end of the CAN

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2c1 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               bus, plug a connector into the unused CAN connector on
               the last device at each

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2c2 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               end of the network with a resistor crimped into the
               appropriate locations.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y2c3 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               22.6COMMUNICATIONS

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2c4 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The CAN standard does not specify high-level message
               protocols. Tritium devices

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2c5 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               use a custom protocol, outlined in the communication
               specification document for

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2c6 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               each device.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2c7 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               By default, each device operates at 500 kbits/second and
               comes programmed

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2c8 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               from the factory with a CAN base address that will allow
               it to work in unison with

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2c9 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               other Tritium devices. The CAN bit rate and base address
               can be set with the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2ca ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Windows BMS configuration software.

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y81 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               22.7POWER SUPPLY

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2cb ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The BMS electronics operate from 12V supplied on the CAN
               bus connector, which

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2cc ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               is switched on by the Tritium EV Driver Controls when it
               is in accessories orrun

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2cd ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               key switch positions.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2ce ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               A second high-current 12V supply connection is present
               for contactor and fan

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2cf ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               operating power, refer to the precharge section of this
               document for more

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2d0 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               details. The CAN Ground and Contactor Supply Ground must
               be both tied to the

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2d1 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               vehicle chassis at some point in the system.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2d2 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The allowable voltage range for both supplies is 10-15V.

            .. container:: t m0 x2c h8 yc ff2 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y2f1 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •SOC and Balance SOC in Ah

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y2f2 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •SOC and Balance SOC in %

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha yf5 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               23.2CMU DATA

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2f3 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The lower section of the program shows telemetry data
               from the CMUs, one row

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y6e ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               per CMU. The information shown is:

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y2f4 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •CMU Serial number

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y70 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •CMU circuit board (PCB) temperature

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y2f5 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •CMU external (cell) temperature

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y72 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •1–8 cell voltage measurements

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2f6 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               The data is highlighted in various ways to quickly
               understand the system status

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y74 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •CMU serial number alternates between a white and light
               blue background

            .. container:: t m0 x9 h4 y2f7 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               each time a packet is received from that CMU

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y2f8 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Trust errors for a cell voltage have a yellow background

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y2f9 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Cells outside the min and max voltage limits have a red
               background

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y2fa ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Cells currently balancing have a blue background

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y2fb ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •The minimum and maximum cells have boldtext

            .. container:: t m0 x8 h4 y2fc ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               •Cells not present (where the CMU has been programmed to
               monitor less

            .. container:: t m0 x9 h4 y2fd ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               than 8 cells) have no text, and a mid-gray background

            .. container:: t m0 x0 ha y2fe ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               23.3COMMAND LINE OPTIONS

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y2ff ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               In addition to double clicking on the executable, the BMS
               Viewing software can

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y300 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               also run from the command line, where certain options can
               be set. The supported

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y301 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               command line options are described below:

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 ybd ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               -s<serial number>

            .. container:: t m0 x9 h4 y302 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               This is used to specify the serial number of the BMU to
               connect to on the

            .. container:: t m0 x9 h4 y303 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               CAN bus when launched

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y304 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               -f<filename>

            .. container:: t m0 x9 h4 y305 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Specifying a filename will enable logging in the
               BMS_Viewer and all data

            .. container:: t m0 x9 h4 y286 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               will logged to the filename.

            .. container:: t m0 x2c h8 yc ff2 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y34 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               -l

            .. container:: t m0 x9 h4 y22a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               Using -l on the command line will enable logging in the
               BMS_Viewer and

            .. container:: t m0 x9 h4 y22b ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               will automatically choose a filename, combining the
               serial number of the

            .. container:: t m0 x9 h4 y22c ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               connected BMU device and the timestamp when the program
               was

            .. container:: t m0 x9 h4 y1b5 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               launched. Note that when using this option that the log
               file will be rolled

            .. container:: t m0 x9 h4 y1b6 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               over at midnight each day.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y137 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               -u<rate>

            .. container:: t m0 x9 h4 y307 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               This option is used to determine the logging rate.
               Currently one can

            .. container:: t m0 x9 h4 y308 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               choose between 0.2, 1, 10, and 60 second update rates.

            .. container:: t m0 x5 h4 y309 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0

               example: BMS\_Viewer.exe -s9566 -l -u10
